    serviceName: "Security Clearance(NoC)",
    serviceDescription:
      " security covers the holistic well-being of an individual, system, entity, organisation or state that allows sovereign choices.",
    serviceLink: "http://scs.rbp.gov.bt/",
    serviceDocument:
      '<p><font face="Times New Roman" size="4"><b style=""><font style=""><span style="color: rgb(4, 1, 1); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">SERVICE NAME:</span><span style="background-color: rgb(0, 150, 255);"><font color="#ffffff">&nbsp;</font></span></font><span style="text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); letter-spacing: 0.0178571em; background-color: rgb(0, 150, 255);"><font color="#ffffff">Security Clearance Systems</font></span></b></font></p><p><font color="#040101"><strong style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; background-color: transparent; text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); letter-spacing: 0.0178571em;"><font size="3" style="">BRIEF DESCRIPTION:</font></strong><br></font></p><p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101"><span>A security clearance is&nbsp;</span><span>a status granted to individuals allowing them access to classified information (state or organizational secrets) or to restricted areas, after completion of a thorough background check</span><span>.</span></font></p><p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101"><strong style="background-color: transparent; text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); letter-spacing: 0.0178571em;">PROCEDURE TO APPLY FOR SCS\\DOCUMENTS REQUIRED:</strong><br></font></p><ul><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Move your mouse over&nbsp;<strong>[Application]</strong>&nbsp;menu and click on</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101"><strong>[New Application]</strong> sub menu.</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">After applying, the status can be tracked by clicking on the&nbsp;<strong>[Track Application]</strong></font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">menu and entering Citizenship Identity Card number.</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">If the application is approved, the applicant need not download and print the</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">certificate. The applicant can proceed to the concerned agency where the certificate</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">will be downloaded, and printed only ofr official record.</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">The Certificate is valid for 1 Year. The applicants can start to renew their Security</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Clearance Certificate, 7 days before the expiry of validity date. For example, if the expiry</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" color="#040101" size="3">date is on 30<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;December, 2011, renewal can be done from 23<sup>rd</sup>&nbsp;December, 2011.</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">The applicants will have to enter their&nbsp;<strong>Date of Birth</strong>, and&nbsp;<strong>Citizenship Identity Card number</strong>&nbsp;as given in the Citizenship Identity Card.</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">If any applicants require hard copy of the Security Clearance Certificate, the applicants may approach to the Bureau of Law and Order, MoHA.</font></li></ul><font color="#040101"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: medium; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.249999px;">SERVICE YOU CAN AVAIL FROM:</span><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><br></font></font><ol><li><a href="https://www.moha.gov.bt/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Final-SCC-Hard-Copy-   Form.docx.pdf" target="_blank">Click here to see the Documents Required for obtaining Security Clearance Certificate in Hard Copy</a><br></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101"><a href="http://119.2.116.21/#" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Click here to view Biometric services available from the Police Stations located in 14 Dzongkhags</a></font></li></ol><p><font color="#040101"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.249999px;"><font size="3">CONTACT INFORMATION:</font></span><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><strong><br></strong></font></font></p><ul><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Royal Bhutan Police, Security Clearance Service: 00975-02-322347 (Ext: 2212/2125)</font></li></ul><ul><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Department of Civil Registration and Census, MoHA: 00975-02-322301 (Ext: 2054)</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101"><span style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); letter-spacing: 0.0178571em;">Bureau of Law and Order, MoHCA: 00975-02-322015 (Ext:2070) OR 00975-02-325173/00975-77190135/00975-77190136 (Ext: 2038)</span></font></li></ul><p class="ql-align-center"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101"><span style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); letter-spacing: 0.0178571em;"><b><i><u>Note:</u> </i></b>Biometric services can now be availed from the Police Stations located in 14 Dzongkhags. Applicants wishing to travel abroad for the purpose of Further Studies/Visa/Employment etc. are requested to get their biometrics done from the following Police Stations in order to avoid huge rush and waiting time at RBP HQs while processing hard copy SCC.</span><br></font></p><ul><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Paro PS</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Punakha PS</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Phuntsholing PS</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Gelephu PS</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Tsirang PS</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Trongsa PS</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Samdrupjongkhar PS</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Trashigang PS</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Mongar PS</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Wangduephodrang PS</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Trashiyangtse PS</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Bumthang PS</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Thimphu PS</font></li><li><font face="Times New Roman" size="3" color="#040101">Samtse PS</font></li></ul>',
